      <title>Remote source database case</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezcopy/forum/general/remote_source_database_case</link>
      <description>Hi,&#13;
&#13;
I'm using your application with ezupgrade and it works perfectly when files and database of the source installation are on the same server.&#13;
However, I've an eZ Publish source instance with a remote MySQL database. In this environment, ezcopy breaks with a database connection problem.&#13;
I suggest these 2 patches.&#13;
&#13;
&lt;b&gt;File : classes/ezcopy.php&lt;/b&gt;&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
17a18&#13;
&gt; 	var $dbHost;&#13;
37c38,40&#13;
&lt; 		&#13;
---&#13;
&gt; &#13;
&gt; 		$this-&gt;dbHost = $this-&gt;cfg-&gt;getSetting('ezcopy', 'DBRoot', 'host');&#13;
&gt; &#13;
842c845,853&#13;
&lt; 		$cmd = "-u " . $this-&gt;dbRootUser;&#13;
---&#13;
&gt; &#13;
&gt; 		$cmd = "";&#13;
&gt; 		&#13;
&gt; 		if($this-&gt;dbHost != '')&#13;
&gt; 		{&#13;
&gt; 			$cmd .= "-h " . $this-&gt;dbHost;&#13;
&gt; 		}&#13;
&gt; &#13;
&gt; 		$cmd .= " -u " . $this-&gt;dbRootUser;&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
&lt;b&gt;File : settings/ezcopy_temmplate.ini&lt;/b&gt;&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
	30a31&#13;
	&gt; host=&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
Hope it's useful.&#13;
Thank you for your application.</description>
