      <title>Error in svn of ezcopy?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezcopy/forum/general/error_in_svn_of_ezcopy</link>
      <description>The topic "ezcopy/ezc installation: 'ezc/Base/base.php'" in the forum for "ezupgrade" appears to be caused by an error in the SVN version of "ezcopy".&#13;
&#13;
The problem is that the file 'ezc/Base/base.php'  is actually to be found at 'ezc/Base/src/base.php'.&#13;
&#13;
I can't find a way of logging this problem, so I'm raising it here.&#13;
&#13;
I obtained a copy of 'ezcopy' from SVN (for 'ezupgrade'), and installed both 'ezupgrade' and 'ezcopy' as described in the install documents. I got the error as described in the 'ezupgrade' forum article. &#13;
&#13;
I changed the path in 'ezcopy/classes/ezcomponents.php' by adding the intermediate 'src' directory and 'ezupgrade' and 'ezcopy' work fine.&#13;
&#13;
Cheers,&#13;
&#13;
Cliff</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (cliffp pratt)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezcopy/forum/general/error_in_svn_of_ezcopy</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Nov 2010 23:20:57 +0000</pubDate>
