    <item>
      <title>Re: Problem with local path</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezcopy/forum/general/problem_with_local_path/re_problem_with_local_path2</link>
      <description>Hi Matthieu,&#13;
&#13;
Thanks for your feedback.&#13;
This is not an app made for making db dumps, this is just a part of the app. The main goal with this app is to download and set up one entire eZ installation locally.&#13;
&#13;
The reason for appending the ssh_user is to separate the installations on the local computer.&#13;
&#13;
Lets say you have set your document root:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$this-&gt;data['document_roort'] = '/var/www/';&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
Then the system will set up the installation for you on /var/www/&lt;username&gt;.&#13;
Thats the main reason for this.&#13;
&#13;
The problem with emptying the cache have we now fixed. This started as a bug when we created ezupgrade. ezupgrade needs ezcopy to work, so we needed to do some adjustments. This should now work.&#13;
&#13;
It now sends inn a path to the eZ installation:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$this-&gt;clearLocalCache( $this-&gt;data['document_root'] . $this-&gt;data['ssh_user'] );&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
function clearLocalCache($path)&#13;
	{&#13;
		$this-&gt;log("Clearing cache ");&#13;
		exec("cd " . $path . ";".$this-&gt;getPathToPHP()." bin/php/ezcache.php --clear-all --purge");&#13;
		$this-&gt;log("OK\n", 'ok');&#13;
	}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Anders Berre)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezcopy/forum/general/problem_with_local_path/re_problem_with_local_path2</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Mar 2010 08:42:56 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
